{"questionId":"13109","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right)\"> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right) = {x^3} + 3{x^2} + 8x - 24\"><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>24</mn></math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>∈</mo> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Prove that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> has only one real zero.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span> (is a zero) &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"display:inline !important;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">A1</span></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Can be seen anywhere.</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>factorise to get&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {x - 3} \\right)\\left( {{x^2} + 8} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + 8 \\ne 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> (for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>)&nbsp;(or equivalent statement)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R1</strong> </em>if correct two complex roots are given.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p'\\left( x \\right) = 3{x^2} - 6x + 8\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>p</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n</math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"display:inline !important;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">A1</span></p>\n<p>attempting to show&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p'\\left( x \\right) \\ne 0\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>p</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em> discriminant = 36 – 96&nbsp;&lt; 0, completing the square</p>\n<p>no turning points<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>only one real zero (as the curve is continuous)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13109","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_10b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Prove that p ( x ) has only one real zero.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}